    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{2}{t^{2}-7t-18}-\frac{t-7}{t^{2}-7t-18}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{1}{t+2}, t\ne 9</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{2}{t^{2}-7t-18}-\frac{t-7}{t^{2}-7t-18}} 
      \amp = \frac{{2-\left(t-7\right)}}{{t^{2}-7t-18}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{2-t+7}}{{\left(t-9\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+2\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-t+9}}{{\left(t-9\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+2\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-\left(t-9\right)}}{{\left(t-9\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+2\right)}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{1}{t+2}, t\ne 9}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>t-9</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>t \ne {9}</m>.</p>
</solution>
